CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 2, 1955, pg. 28 reads: "Free Prizes, Samples nad Demonstrations Galore...2. The enormous May-Stern Company Food Freezer Plan booth was represented by Joe Strickler, manager, center, and left to right, Mrs. Elsie Chue, Mrs. Nedra Banner, Mr. Weems, Miss Hedda Remic, Edward Kay and Harry Pancoast...Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left, seated: Elsie Chue, Nedra Banner, Hedda Remic, and Harry Pancoast; standing: Mr. Weems, Joe Strickler, and Edward Kay, gathered in Philco refrigerator and freezers booth in the Syria Mosque for the 1955 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
